Exercise

1. Which variables contain missing values?

Education, leave (dont know are not coded)

names(bes)
## [1] "vote"      "leave"     "education" "age"
dim(bes[is.na(bes$vote),])
## [1] 0 4
dim(bes[is.na(bes$leave),])
## [1] 2851    4
dim(bes[is.na(bes$education),])
## [1] 3425    4
dim(bes[is.na(bes$age),])
## [1] 0 4
2. How many dont know responses are in the dataset?

2851

3. What is the percentage of respondents who answered leave?

44.3%

prop.table(table(bes$vote))
## 
## don't know      leave       stay won't vote 
## 0.07489885 0.44317851 0.46454119 0.01738145
4. What is the percentage of respondents who answered dont know?

7.4%

5. Plot the distribution of answers in the vote column
barplot(prop.table(table(bes$vote)), ylim=c(0,0.5), xlab="Answers", ylab='Proportion', 
        main="Attitudes Towards Brexit")

6. What is the average age of the respondents

50.7

mean(bes$age)
## [1] 50.75025
7. What percent of respondents in the data set are over 60? (tip: Use logical operators >, <, ==, !=, <=, >=)

34%

dim(bes[bes$age > 60,])[1]/dim(bes)[1] 
## [1] 0.34067
8. What percent of respondents in the data set are exactly 60 years old?

2.4%

dim(bes[bes$age == 60,])[1]/dim(bes)[1]
## [1] 0.02401683
9. What percent of respondents in the data set are NOT 60 years old?

97.5%

dim(bes[bes$age != 60,])[1]/dim(bes)[1]
## [1] 0.9759832
10. What is the distribution of age? Do you notice anything? (tip: use hist() and boxplot())
hist(bes$age)

boxplot(bes$age)

11. Examine distribution of age of brexit supporters and non-supporters. What do you notice?
hist(bes$age[bes$vote == 'leave'])

hist(bes$age[bes$vote == 'stay'])

12. Check distribution of brexit non-supporters by education levels

(tip: first use na.omit() because education variable contains NAs; second, create a dummy variable 1 indicating leave, 0 for rest; third, use prop.table to see a two-way proportions table)

bes1<-na.omit(bes)
dim(bes1)
## [1] 25097     4
dim(bes1[complete.cases(bes1),])
## [1] 25097     4
bes1$leave<-ifelse(bes1$vote=='leave',1,0)
head(bes1)
